item.description:
This term was inherited from the migration of NIFSTD-Anatomy to Uberon. Upon consideration the same concept is better represented by existing classes in Uberon such as "membrnous organ". The following comment was inherited from http://uri.neuinfo.org/nif/nifstd/ Not sure this is the correct designation; FMA has "membranous organ" but that doesn't seem quite right either.
Consider: UBERON:0000158, http://uri.neuinfo.org/nif/nifstd/nlx_anat_090201
